parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal support assembly can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, leading to difficulty starting the vehicle, loss of control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle lurches forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axles can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Axle failure
loss of vehicle control
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty head gasket can cause engine overheating, leading to severe engine damage, and potentially resulting in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or breakdowns.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
blows a head gasket
antifreeze leaks into the engine block
white smoke is emitted from the exhaust system
and the engine runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause unexpected and sudden inflation of the airbag, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also cause distractions, loss of control, and unexpected movements of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
airbag light comes on
airbag deploys while vehicle is in idle or parked
airbag deploys without any impact or crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
airbag light does not come on
airbag system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbag sensors can cause unintended airbag deployment or failure to deploy airbags, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag light comes on
airbag sensors malfunction
airbag system fails to function properly.
